      <item>
        <title>Password change bug</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Hexagon]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Let’s have a look at what’s happening:</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="4" data-topic="3987">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/lana/40/444_1.png" class="avatar"> Lana:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>sudo su</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p><code>sudo</code> asks for your <strong>user</strong> password and runs <code>su</code> as <code>root</code>. <code>su</code> changes your current user to be <code>root</code> (<code>su</code> doesn’t ask for a password again as it’s executed as root).</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="4" data-topic="3987">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/lana/40/444_1.png" class="avatar"> Lana:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>passwd</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>this will change your <strong>root</strong> password as you are <code>root</code> right now.</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="4" data-topic="3987">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/lana/40/444_1.png" class="avatar"> Lana:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>su user</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>changes to the <code>user</code> user (you could also enter <code>exit</code> to leave the session as <code>root</code>, no password asked for <code>su</code> because you are root right now)</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="4" data-topic="3987">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/lana/40/444_1.png" class="avatar"> Lana:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>sudo su</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p><code>sudo</code> asks again for your <strong>user</strong> password which is still <code>changeme</code> as you’ve changed only the root password. (if you enter just <code>su</code> without <code>sudo</code> you will be asked for your new root password)</p>
<hr>
<p>The solution for your problem: just execute “<code>passwd</code>” as <code>user</code> or “<code>passwd user</code>” as <code>root</code>.</p>
<p>See also the corresponding wiki entry: <a href="https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Post_Install_Advice#Change_Passwords" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Post_Install_Advice#Change_Passwords</a></p>
          <p><a href="http://forums.whonix.org/t/password-change-bug/3987/5">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
        <link>http://forums.whonix.org/t/password-change-bug/3987/5</link>
